 According to a police report, Samson Njenga, 41, and Ngare Wanjiku. 34, were nabbed on Monday evening in possession of transformer oil, an assortment of spanners in their house. Detectives further said that some copper coils which the two are believed to have stolen have already been transported to Nairobi and Nakuru. The duo is suspected to be a part of a ring of gangsters said to have been vandalizing Kenya Power transmission equipment. The power supplier has additionally dispatched a team to join police and detectives in ongoing investigations.